## Analytics conventions
- Global event names: `lib/src/core/monitoring/analytics/analytics_events.dart`
- Feature-specific events: `lib/src/features/<feature>/domain/analytics/<feature>_events.dart`

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — user_config feature events in domain/analytics/user_config_events.dart
final class SetAppThemeModeUseCaseEvent extends AnalyticsEvent {
  factory SetAppThemeModeUseCaseEvent.success() => ...
  factory SetAppThemeModeUseCaseEvent.failure({required Map<String, dynamic> properties}) => ...
}

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded string outside constants class
Analytics.track(AnalyticsEvent(name: 'theme_changed'));

// ❌ BAD — analytics in BLoC (ThemeBloc, LocaleBloc, etc.)
// analytics only belong in UseCase call() methods
```

- `Analytics.track(...)` is only permitted inside `UseCase.call()` implementations
- `AnalyticsEventNames` and `AnalyticsPropertyKeys` constants must be used — no raw strings

## Context extensions
`core/utils/extensions/context_x.dart` provides convenience properties on `BuildContext`.
Always use them — never call the underlying Flutter APIs directly.

| Property | Returns | ❌ Never use |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `context.theme` | `ThemeData` | `Theme.of(context)` |
| `context.textTheme` | `TextTheme` | `Theme.of(context).textTheme` |
| `context.colorScheme` | `ColorScheme` | `ColorScheme.of(context)` / `Theme.of(context).colorScheme` |
| `context.baseThemeX` | `BaseThemeExtension` | `theme.extension<BaseThemeExtension>()!` |
| `context.l10n` | `AppLocalizations` | `AppLocalizations.of(context)` |
| `context.assets` | `AppContextAssets` | `AppAssets...` in widgets |
| `context.locale` | `Locale` | `Localizations.localeOf(context)` |
| `context.languageCode` | `String` | `Localizations.localeOf(context).languageCode` |
| `context.isRTL` | `bool` | manual `['ar','he','fa','ur'].contains(...)` check |

## Typedefs
`core/utils/typedef.dart` defines shared type aliases. Use them everywhere:

| Alias | Expands to |
|-------|-----------|
| `FutureEither<T>` | `Future<Either<Failure, T>>` |
| `StreamEither<T>` | `Stream<Either<Failure, T>>` |
| `DataMap` | `Map<String, dynamic>` |
